As of the [[census]] of 2010, there are 117 people, 60 households, and 34 families residing in the town. The racial makeup of the town is majority White (93.2% or 107 persons). 5.1% (or 6 persons) are [[Mexicans|Mexican]]; and 3.4% (4 persons) are [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] with 2 people identifying solely as Native American and 2 others identifying as also White. There are 0.00% [[African American]] and 0.00% [[Asia]]n or Pacific Islander.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3766740| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212142118/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3766740| url-status=dead| archive-date=February 12, 2020| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (DP-1): Tar Heel town, North Carolina| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| access-date=February 6, 2014}}</ref>

